email subject: Information Needed - Your Optiver Application
email body: Hi Muskan, Thank you for applying to our Future Focus 2025 program. Unfortunately, we have reached capacity and are no longer accepting additional candidates. While the Future Focus program is closed, we are still accepting applications for our Insight Days - Women in Tech & Trading program , which will occur April 10 - 11. I've included for you more information about this program below. If you would like to transfer your application to our Insight Days program, please respond to this email by Thursday, February 6th. We will follow up with the next steps at that point! Insight Days – Women in Tech & Trading Timing : This program is two days, Thursday, April 10 – Friday, April 11. email subject: Update from the D. E. Shaw group on your Fellowship application
email body: Hi Muskan, Thank you for your interest in the D. E. Shaw group’s fellowship program. We’ve reviewed your application and, while we were impressed by your qualifications, we’re unable to offer you a spot in our upcoming March fellowships. We hope to stay in touch, and we’d like to invite you to participate in an upcoming virtual information session on Thursday, April 10, at 4:00 PM ET, to learn more about our firm. If you’re interested in attending, please fill out this registration form. Keep an eye out for our internship applications opening on Monday, January 27 for Discretionary Investing and Strategy and Business Development roles. Applications for our Business Operations, Systematic Investing, and Systems internships will open in June. You can learn more about internship opportunities at the firm here ; fellowships are not the only way folks can learn about who we are and what we do. Thank you again for your application. Wishing you all the best this academic year! Best, Cody Marshall (he/him) Recruiting | The D. E. Shaw Group

email subject: Update on your Futureforce Tech Launchpad Pre-Internship application
email body: Hi Muskan, We are grateful for your enthusiasm towards the 2025 Salesforce’s Futureforce Tech Launchpad (FTL) program, powered by CodePath. We acknowledge the time and energy you dedicated to your application and regret to inform you that we are unable to offer you a seat in this year's program. We received an overwhelming number of applications from talented students all over the country, and regretfully, we have limited seats available, which has made the selection process challenging. We wanted to reach out to you as soon as possible so you can plan your next steps accordingly. We understand that receiving this news may be disappointing, and we want to assure you that this does not reflect your abilities or potential. As a result of the high volume of applications, we are unable to provide feedback on your application at this time. However, we encourage you to explore www.codepath.org/courses to learn about our other no-cost programs. Enrollment in our Spring 2025 courses is still open until January 26th, and we highly recommend that you consider applying to one of our courses. The admissions process varies for every program. Thank you again for your interest in Salesforce’s Futureforce Tech Launchpad (FTL) program. We wish you all the best in your future endeavors. All the best, CodePath Office of Admissions

email subject: Update on your Software Engineer Intern Summer 2025 application with Toast
email body: Hi Muskan, We appreciate your interest in the Software Engineer Intern Summer 2025 position at Toast. You chose to pursue a career with us and for that, we are incredibly honored and grateful. We love everything that you bring to the table, however we received other applicants who more closely match our needs at this time. We know that messages like this are never fun to receive, but we mean it when we say that we’d love to stay connected. We invite you to join the Toast Talent Network. By completing this short form, you’ll help our recruiting team understand which opportunities best align with your skills and interests. You can also always check out our careers site , where you can see all open positions, learn more about our teams, and visit the Life at Toast blog. We also encourage you to keep up with Toast by checking out our LinkedIn and Instagram pages! We wish you all the best! Toasting to you, Toast Recruiting

email subject: You have successfully submitted your IBM job application.
email body: IBM Careers Thank you for applying Muskan Mahajan, thank you for applying to the role of Back End Developer Intern: 2025 Ref:722759BR at IBM. We’re excited that you’re considering us as your next employer! Here at IBM, we believe our greatest asset is the IBMer. We strive every day to foster a culture of conscious inclusion for all individuals and provide IBMers the opportunity to make a positive impact on the world while bringing their authentic selves to work. To that end, we want to be as transparent as possible with you about what to expect next now that you’ve applied to IBM. Currently, your application is being reviewed by real IBMers, who are experts in screening resumes in their respective fields. If there's a potential match, we’ll contact you to discuss the next steps of our hiring process. While you wait to hear from us: • Visit our special careers page to find tips on acing your interview and career advice from current IBMers. You can also check out our application process page to learn more about how we hire at IBM. • Connect with us on our Life@IBM social media channels (links in the footer below) where you can engage with us further, discover what life at IBM is like, and see how IBMers around the world are making an impact. You can also check the status of your application at any time by visiting your IBM Career Portal . email body: Your application has been submitted! If there's a match, we will make an email introduction. Software Engineer Intern Sponsor a Pet · Atlanta · Austin · Boston · California · Chicago · Los Angeles · New York City · Philadelphia · Phoenix · Washington DC · San Francisco · Reston · Raleigh · Charlotte · Remote $1-2K You applied today You should hear back in 1-2 weeks Schedule your first interview View my application Browse more jobs In the meantime You can update your profile before your application is reviewed. Read up on on how to make your profile stand out even more Check out the other unique startup jobs on Wellfound Sponsor a Pet We are a fundraising company for animal non-profits Actively Hiring Early Stage Location Washington DC Founders Scott DeFries Company size 11-50 Benefits Remote friendly, Volunteer opportunities Sponsor a Pet is a fundraising platform, dedicated to providing Animal Non-Profits a platform to share their stories and help raise the necessary resources to save the lives of animals. We do this by working together with passionate local organizations to amplify our impact in communities as we come together as one. The mission of Sponsor a Pet is to provide every animal a loving environment that they can call home. Every animal deserves the opportunity to have their basic needs met; food, medicine, a safe and loving family. Our overarching goals are to eliminate Kill Shelters, Animal Abuse, and the destruction of their habitats. We strive to share stories of positivity, laughter, uplifting stories, animals who need our help, and to give thanks to the volunteers who work tirelessly to help find these animals find their forever home. If this resonates with you, join our team and lets grow our community! Who We Are We are passionate individuals who came to together under a common vision to help all animals. We understand working together, moving in the same direction will have a greater impact. Sponsor a Pet provides an audience across the country that local non-profits do not have access to. As we come together we can create a lasting impact in all of our communities. How to get Involved Singing up as one of our members as a PetStar is a great Start. On top of that, there’s much more you can do to get involved. The easiest way is to share your story with us. We would love to hear from you and share your story. What drives your passion for animals and a little about your background. Another way would be to share local organizations that need our help, or local communities who would want to get involved. Our goal is to provide a platform for animals, non-profits, Individuals, and companies alike. We are thrilled that we will be welcoming 650 students into Cohort 4, offering two distinct learning pathways. This assessment will allow us to understand your aptitude and foundational coding skills. It can be completed at your convenience and is estimated to take no more than 120 minutes. email subject: Thank You for Applying to the Software Engineering Intern at Intuitive.
email body: Hi Muskan, On behalf of the Intuitive team, we would like to thank you for your interest in our company and the time you took to apply for the Software Engineering Intern role. Your application and the associated documents will be reviewed by the University Hiring Program Team and if there is a match, a member of the team will contact you to discuss next steps. We understand that looking for an internship can be daunting and time consuming. While we can’t promise that you will hear back immediately, we can promise that we will review applicants fairly and consider your qualifications throughout the entire recruiting season. We believe that setting appropriate expectations and being transparent is a good start. To that end, here’s what you can expect: Internship recruiting season at Intuitive spans through Fall, Winter and Spring. We ensure that all opportunities are posted on the career site, and every applicant is assessed against the unique relevant qualifications for each internship role. Every hiring team proceeds to interviews at different points in the recruiting season, so if you have not heard back, your application is still in consideration. While we review your application, we encourage you to visit the Careers Page and stay engaged with us by signing up for job alert and joining our Talent Community . Best Regards, Intuitive Talent Acquisition Team Access My Application Please do not share or forward this email, as it pertains to your specific job application

email subject: Thank You for Your Application – Let's Stay Connected
email body: ​​​​​​​​​​ Hi Muskan, Thank you for applying for theUTG - Software Engineer Internships - Summer 2025 position at ServiceNow. We appreciate the effort you put into your application and your enthusiasm for joining our team. While your skills and background are impressive, we have decided to move forward with another candidate for this role. This was not an easy decision as we received applications from many talented individuals, including you. We believe in the power of people and their potential to make a difference. Our culture and People Pact reflect our commitment to fostering an environment where everyone feels valued, respected, and empowered to grow. We hope that you consider other roles at ServiceNow in the future. You can visit our Careers Page and apply for new opportunities based on your career aspirations and qualifications. Stay engaged with Now Learning to build in-demand ServiceNow skills through self-paced courses and real-time training sessions. And remember to follow us on our ServiceNow LinkedIn page to stay connected. Thank you for your interest in ServiceNow, and we invite you to join our Talent Community for company updates. Sincerely, The ServiceNow Talent Acquisition Team

email subject: Your TechWise Program Application: Next Step
email body: Dear Muskan Mahajan, Hope this email finds you in great spirits! Thank you for your application to the TechWise program. We are thrilled that we will be welcoming 650 students into Cohort 4, offering two distinct learning pathways. Next Step: Complete the Online Assessment To proceed with your application, we request that you complete the online assessment. This assessment will allow us to understand your aptitude and foundational coding skills. It can be completed at your convenience and is estimated to take no more than 120 minutes. Completion of the online assessment is essential for consideration in the next stage of the selection process. We encourage you to complete it as soon as possible. Please write to techwise@talentsprint.com if you have any questions. Looking forward to welcoming you to Cohort 4 of TechWise. All the best! Regards Team TechWise TalentSprint

email subject: Thank You for Your Application
email body: Hello Muskan, Thank you for expressing your interest in a career with Intel Corporation. We are thrilled to be considered as your potential employer. email subject: Application Received: Futureforce Tech Launchpad (FTL)
email body: Hi Muskan, We just wanted to let you know that your application for Salesforce’s Futureforce Tech Launchpad, powered by CodePath, has been received and is now being reviewed. Thank you for your interest and we look forward to learning more about you! All students will be notified of their status by January 22 . Course Details Reminder: Sessions run from June 3 - August 9, 2025 for 10 weeks. Students are expected to participate daily, Monday-Friday, from 9am to 5pm PT. This program will take place at Salesforce's San Francisco office. Travel and relocation expenses for the duration of the program will be covered. Please note that full attendance and participation are required in the program. Students will attend class, complete weekly exercises and labs, and apply their learning to additional projects. If you are no longer able to participate, you can go to your application dashboard anytime to cancel your application. Sincerely, CodePath.org Office of Admissions

email subject: Your application - Software Engineer - Summer Intern at Datadog
email body: Hi Muskan, Thanks again for your interest in Datadog and the Software Engineer - Summer Intern role. We sincerely appreciate you taking the time to apply with us, but we have decided not to move forward with your application at this time. Although this opportunity didn’t work out, we would be happy to reconsider your candidacy in the future. We make a point of revisiting past applications on a regular basis to match them to newly opened jobs, and will keep your information handy for future opportunities. Your applicant information will always be processed in accordance with our Applicant and Candidate Privacy Policy . In the meantime, we encourage you to explore the following as you prepare to enter the job market: Expand on your extracurriculars, e.g. internships, hackathons, open-source projects, clubs, leadership roles, research. Continue to challenge yourself in your coursework to hone your technical skills. Meet with your school’s career services center to help you revamp your resume, prep for interviews, or work through your priorities as you’re applying to different companies. We typically post early-career positions by September, so we encourage you to visit our job postings periodically via our early careers page . Stay in the loop and join our early-career talent community ! You can also learn more about #datadoglife from our employees on LinkedIn and Instagram . Also, if you didn't already know, students can use Datadog for free through the Github Student Developer Pack . We wish you the best of luck in your job search. Sincerely, The Datadog Campus Recruiting Team PS: If you've applied to multiple roles at Datadog, you may hear from us more than once.

email subject: Thank you for applying to Twilio!
email body: Hi Muskan, Thank you for your interest in a role at Twilio! We just received your application. We know that job hunting can be stressful. Our intention is to be transparent about our hiring process to help you succeed. On that note, let's talk a bit about our hiring process. Reviewing Your Application Rather than relying on bots and algorithms, Twilio has human recruiters reviewing every application, so it can take a little longer than automated screening. Also, there are no loose ends with us: we'll let you know where you stand either way. Our Interview Process If we like what we see, a recruiting team member will reach out to discuss the opportunity. The next steps could include a few rounds of interviews taking from 2-4 weeks, sometimes longer. While this email doesn't guarantee an interview, we encourage you to check out our Interview Prep Guide . Even if you don't move forward with us, it's got some great tips for active job seekers. And to get a feel for the Twilio experience, check out our culture page and follow our LinkedIn . Thanks again for your interest in building the future of communications! Thank you, -Twilio Recruiting Team #WeBuildAtTwilio

email subject: Your IBM Application: Next Steps
email body: Dear Muskan Mahajan, We are excited to see that you have applied for a position at IBM, and we want to ensure that you have the best opportunity to showcase your fantastic skills. We understand that resume alone doesn't always reflect a candidate's full potential. That's why we invite you to complete one or more of the following assessments, which will help us gain a more comprehensive view of your capabilities. IBM values accessibility and are committed to ensuring that every candidate has an equal opportunity to showcase their skills and potential. We support measures like additional time for persons with disabilities on selection assessments. We use following assessments for selection purposes. You will be invited to complete 1 or more of these assessments, depending on the role you are applying for. The next step in the process includes one or more assessments – described below. The Coding Assessment - helps us to understand your level of programming knowledge and ability. You will be presented with a coding interface to solve coding challenges. This is a timed assessment. We believe that these assessments will provide you with a better opportunity to showcase your skills, and we encourage you to take them seriously. We also want to make sure that you feel comfortable and supported throughout the process. All applicants are requested to click the accommodation link below. If you are a person with a disability, please follow the link to submit any adjustments that you require, such as extra time. IBM will review the details of your requirement and work with you on any adjustment options for your application. It is important that you submit your requirements before starting any assessments. If you do not need extra time on the assessments, please mark your response in the link below. Accommodation Form Please note that this form must be completed for each position you apply for that requires an assessment. For additional information and helpful tips, please visit our blog We appreciate your interest in joining our team and wish you the best of luck as you complete these assessments. We can't wait to see all that you have to offer! Sincerely, The IBM Talent Acquisition Team 727588BR Software Engineer - Large Scale Language Models Intern: 2025

We strive every day to foster a culture of conscious inclusion for all individuals and provide IBMers the opportunity to make a positive impact on the world while bringing their authentic selves to work. To that end, we want to be as transparent as possible with you about what to expect next now that you’ve applied to IBM. Currently, your application is being reviewed by real IBMers, who are experts in screening resumes in their respective fields. If there's a potential match, we’ll contact you to discuss the next steps of our hiring process. email subject: Your application - Product Manager - Intern at Datadog
email body: Hi Muskan, Thanks again for your interest in Datadog and the Product Manager - Intern role. We sincerely appreciate you taking the time to apply with us, but we have decided not to move forward with your application at this time. Although this opportunity didn’t work out, we would be happy to reconsider your candidacy in the future. We make a point of revisiting past applications on a regular basis to match them to newly opened jobs and will keep your information handy for future opportunities. Your applicant information will always be processed in accordance with our Applicant and Candidate Privacy Policy . In the meantime, we encourage you to explore the following as you prepare to enter the job market: Expand on your extracurriculars, e.g. internships, projects, clubs, leadership roles, research. Continue to challenge yourself in your coursework to hone your technical skills. Meet with your school’s career services center to help you revamp your resume, prep for interviews, or work through your priorities as you’re applying to different companies. We typically post early-career positions by September, so we encourage you to visit our job postings periodically via our early careers page . Stay in the loop and join our early-career talent community ! You can also learn more about #datadoglife from our employees on LinkedIn and Instagram . Also, if you didn't already know, students can use Datadog for free through the Github Student Developer Pack . We wish you the best of luck in your job search. Sincerely, The Datadog Campus Recruiting Team PS: If you've applied to multiple roles at Datadog, you may hear from us more than once.

email subject: Thank you for applying to Braze!
email body: Hi Muskan, Thank you for your application for the Software Engineering Intern position! At Braze, we’re all about igniting the passion of our 1,500+ employees and empowering them to solve great challenges through creative innovation, so we’re thrilled to hear you’re interested in joining us. Our Talent Team is working hard reviewing our rapidly growing number of applications. If your skills and experience match what we’re looking for, standby for a reach out from our team. If not, we’d love to keep you in mind for future opportunities. So, we’ll be sure to hang on to your resume (and we promise not to keep it too long to protect your privacy). In the meanwhile, you can keep up with Braze Life by following us on LinkedIn and Instagram , or by taking a look at our careers page. Best, The Braze Talent Team Note: No need to reply – there’s nobody home at this inbox!

email subject: [Reminder] Jamboard application wind down
email body: The Jamboard application will wind down on Dec 31, 2024 Dear Jamboard user, This is a reminder that the Jamboard application will begin winding down on December 31, 2024 . After this day, we will begin deleting Jamboard files. What you need to know December 31, 2024 Last day to migrate your Jams to a supported partner application. After this day, we will begin the final shutdown process and Jams will be deleted over the next several weeks. What you need to do Our records show that you have recently used the Jamboard app or have at least 1 Jam in your Google Drive. We recommend backing up your Jam files by migrating them to one of our partners. Learn more about our partners below and how you can import your Jams to continue working on your whiteboards: FigJam by Figma Lucidspark by Lucid Software Miro We’re here to help For more information, you can visit our FAQ page . Thanks for choosing Google Workspace. —The Google Workspace Team Was this information helpful? © 2024 Google LLC 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043 You have received this mandatory email announcement to update you about important information related to your Google account.

email subject: Finish next steps for your Google application
email body: Note: Please disregard if you’ve completed both the Snapshot survey and coding exercise within the past 24 hours. Dear Muskan Mahajan, Thanks again for applying for the role of Software Engineering Intern, BS, Summer 2025 - United States. We sent you an email 4 days ago with links to the Snapshot survey and coding exercise. The deadline to finish these is coming up and we don’t want you to miss this chance at becoming the next great Googler. Please complete both the Snapshot survey and coding exercise by 11:59pm PT on Oct 21, 2024 . We can only consider your application for this role if both are completed by the deadline. The Snapshot survey and coding exercise questions, along with your responses and your solutions, are for your eyes only . Do not forward or share them. Instructions 1. Complete the Snapshot survey : Tell us more about your skills, experience, and work preferences in a ~15-minute survey. 2. Complete the coding exercise : Give us a sense of your coding skills in this 90-minute exercise. You’ll solve two problems using your choice of C, C++, C#, Go, Java, JavaScript, or Python languages. Here are some important guidelines: Practice first : Get some practice before you start the coding exercise by clicking "Practice first" on the welcome page. We highly recommend practicing before starting the actual coding exercise. [Important] In order to access the coding exercise : Your browser needs to be logged into the same email address you were logged into that first time you accessed the coding exercise. Please also try using an incognito window in Chrome or Safari. If you are still experiencing issues, please let us know. Do not code in multiple windows : This could lead to an incorrect submission of your solutions. Be mindful of time : You have 90 minutes to complete two problems. Make sure to set aside enough time; the timer begins as soon as you click "Start timed exercise." Use research : Official documentation and standard libraries can help with structure, syntax, and/or diction. Using them is allowed and encouraged. Only submit your own work : We want to learn more about your skills, not someone else’s. Solutions or source code that come from blogs, your friends, coworkers, professors, etc., won't be reviewed. Questions or Issues? Please send an email to assessment-help@google.com, add "[Scaled Assessment]" in the subject line of your email, and include your: Name Email Address Question or description of the issue and any relevant screenshots Please report technical issues as soon as possible : We can help you with technical problems within 24 hours of starting the coding exercise, but not after. Accommodations We value inclusiveness and understand there are many ways to process information. If you require an accommodation due to a medical condition, disability, or neurodivergence, please send an email to assessment-help@google.com to request a specific accommodation or determine what options may be available. Please also add “[Scaled Assessment]” in the subject line of your email. Let us know your accommodation needs before engaging in or completing the assessment. Accommodations include, but are not limited to: Extra time to complete the assessment Guidance on screen reader resources: Google Accessibility - built in screen reader Browser URL: https://support.google.com/accessibility/answer/7031755?hl=en#zippy=%2Cchoose-text-with-your-cursor Microsoft - Narrator Browser URL: https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/complete-guide-to-narrator-e4397a0d-ef4f-b386-d8ae-c172f109bdb1 There is no need to provide us with the nature of or reason for your request for accommodations at this time. Any information you do provide us regarding your health is provided with your explicit consent to our using such information to assess your accommodation request. You can withdraw that consent at any time by sending a subsequent email to assessment-help@google.com . Please also add “[Scaled Assessment]” in the subject line of your email. However, if you withdraw consent before we have made an assessment we may not be able to provide you with an accommodation. Confidentiality: The information you provide in an accommodation request will only be reviewed by our global disability partner, EmployAbility, in order to assess and provide you with reasonable accommodations. Google does not require a diagnosis, treatment plan, or Government disability certificate. Thanks! Google Recruiting FAQs: Can I have an extension? To keep our process fair, we ask that everyone complete both the Snapshot survey and coding exercise by the deadline. If you have a scheduling conflict that absolutely can't be moved, let us know as soon as possible by emailing assessment-help@google.com and we're happy to talk through options. How will I know if my code is submitted? After you submit your solutions, you’ll be redirected to a confirmation page that shows how many questions and lines of code you submitted as well as the language your code was submitted in. When will I get feedback about my coding exercise? We’re not able to provide any specific feedback on your coding exercise, but someone from our staffing team will be in touch after we’ve had a chance to review your entire application, including your Snapshot survey and coding exercise. Please note, if you hear from someone before you’ve completed the Snapshot survey and coding exercise, you’ll still need to finish them by the deadline. Are there system/browser requirements to complete the survey and coding exercise? A consistent internet connection is essential for an optimal experience. We recommend testing your internet connection using our Measurement Lab tool to ensure it's stable. Please use the latest version of one of these browsers: Chrome, Firefox, Microsoft Edge, Microsoft Internet Explorer, Safari. Unable to access the coding exercise? Your browser needs to be logged into the same email address you were logged into that first time you accessed the coding exercise. Please also try using an incognito window in your browser If you are still experiencing issues, please let us know. Google Inc. 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA. 94043 You have received this email because of your recent application to Google.

email subject: Your IBM Application: Next Steps
email body: Dear Muskan Mahajan, We are excited to see that you have applied for a position at IBM, and we want to ensure that you have the best opportunity to showcase your fantastic skills. We understand that resume alone doesn't always reflect a candidate's full potential. That's why we invite you to complete one or more of the following assessments, which will help us gain a more comprehensive view of your capabilities. IBM values accessibility and are committed to ensuring that every candidate has an equal opportunity to showcase their skills and potential. We support measures like additional time for persons with disabilities on selection assessments. We use following assessments for selection purposes. You will be invited to complete 1 or more of these assessments, depending on the role you are applying for. The next step in the process includes one or more assessments – described below. The Coding Assessment - helps us to understand your level of programming knowledge and ability. You will be presented with a coding interface to solve coding challenges. This is a timed assessment. We believe that these assessments will provide you with a better opportunity to showcase your skills, and we encourage you to take them seriously. We also want to make sure that you feel comfortable and supported throughout the process. All applicants are requested to click the accommodation link below. If you are a person with a disability, please follow the link to submit any adjustments that you require, such as extra time. IBM will review the details of your requirement and work with you on any adjustment options for your application. It is important that you submit your requirements before starting any assessments. If you do not need extra time on the assessments, please mark your response in the link below. Accommodation Form Please note that this form must be completed for each position you apply for that requires an assessment. For additional information and helpful tips, please visit our blog We appreciate your interest in joining our team and wish you the best of luck as you complete these assessments. We can't wait to see all that you have to offer! Sincerely, The IBM Talent Acquisition Team 729592BR Data for LLMs - Software Engineer Intern: 2025

email subject: Next steps for your Google application
email body: Dear Muskan Mahajan, Thanks again for applying for the role of Software Engineering Intern, BS, Summer 2025 - United States. To help us get to know you, we invite you to complete a Snapshot survey and a coding exercise (see below). Please complete both the Snapshot survey and coding exercise by 11:59pm PT on Oct 21, 2024 . We can only consider your application for this role if both are completed by the deadline. The Snapshot survey and coding exercise questions, along with your responses and solutions, are for your eyes only . Do not forward or share them. Instructions 1. Complete the Snapshot survey : Tell us more about your skills, experience, and work preferences in a ~15-minute survey. 2. Complete the coding exercise : Give us a sense of your coding skills in this 90-minute exercise. You’ll solve two problems using your choice of C, C++, C#, Go, Java, JavaScript, or Python languages. Here are some important guidelines: Practice first : Get some practice before you start the coding exercise by clicking "Practice first" on the welcome page. We highly recommend practicing before starting the actual coding exercise. [Important] In order to access the coding exercise : Your browser needs to be logged into the same email address you were logged into that first time you accessed the coding exercise. Please also try using an incognito window in Chrome or Safari. If you are still experiencing issues, please let us know. Do not code in multiple windows : This could lead to an incorrect submission of your solutions. Be mindful of time : You have 90 minutes to complete two problems. Make sure to set aside enough time; the timer begins as soon as you click "Start timed exercise." Use research : Official documentation and standard libraries can help with structure, syntax, and/or diction. Using them is allowed and encouraged. Only submit your own work : We want to learn more about your skills, not someone else’s. Solutions or source code that come from blogs, your friends, coworkers, professors, etc., won't be reviewed. Questions or Issues? Please send an email to assessment-help@google.com, add "[Scaled Assessment]" in the subject line of your email, and include your Name Email Address Question or description of the issue and any relevant screenshots Please report technical issues as soon as possible : We can help you with technical problems within 24 hours of starting the coding exercise, but not after. Accommodations We value inclusiveness and understand there are many ways to process information. If you require an accommodation due to a medical condition, disability, or neurodivergence, please send an email to assessment-help@google.com to request a specific accommodation or determine what options may be available. Please also add “[Scaled Assessment]” in the subject line of your email. Let us know your accommodation needs before engaging in or completing the assessment. Accommodations include, but are not limited to: Extra time to complete the assessment Guidance on screen reader resources: Google Accessibility - built in screen reader Browser URL: https://support.google.com/accessibility/answer/7031755?hl=en#zippy=%2Cchoose-text-with-your-cursor Microsoft - Narrator Browser URL: https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/complete-guide-to-narrator-e4397a0d-ef4f-b386-d8ae-c172f109bdb1 There is no need to provide us with the nature of or reason for your request for accommodations at this time. Any information you do provide us regarding your health is provided with your explicit consent to our using such information to assess your accommodation request. You can withdraw that consent at any time by sending a subsequent email to assessment-help@google.com . Please also add “[Scaled Assessment]” in the subject line of your email. However, if you withdraw consent before we have made an assessment we may not be able to provide you with an accommodation. Confidentiality: The information you provide in an accommodation request will only be reviewed by our global disability partner, EmployAbility, in order to assess and provide you with reasonable accommodations. Google does not require a diagnosis, treatment plan, or Government disability certificate. Thanks! Google Recruiting FAQs: Can I have an extension? To keep our process fair, we ask that everyone complete both the Snapshot survey and coding exercise by the deadline. If you have a scheduling conflict that absolutely can't be moved, let us know as soon as possible by emailing assessment-help@google.com and we're happy to talk through options. How will I know if my code is submitted? After you submit your solutions, you’ll be redirected to a confirmation page that shows how many questions and lines of code you submitted as well as the language your code was submitted in. When will I get feedback about my coding exercise? We’re not able to provide any specific feedback on your coding exercise, but someone from our staffing team will be in touch after we’ve had a chance to review your entire application, including your Snapshot survey and coding exercise. Please note, if you hear from someone before you’ve completed the Snapshot survey and coding exercise, you’ll still need to finish them by the deadline. Are there system/browser requirements to complete the survey and coding exercise? A consistent internet connection is essential for an optimal experience. We recommend testing your internet connection using our Measurement Lab tool to ensure it's stable. Please use the latest version of one of these browsers: Chrome, Firefox, Microsoft Edge, Microsoft Internet Explorer, Safari. Unable to access the coding exercise? Your browser needs to be logged into the same email address you were logged into that first time you accessed the coding exercise. Please also try using an incognito window in your browser If you are still experiencing issues, please let us know. Google Inc. 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA. 94043 You have received this email because of your recent application to Google.

email subject: Harvard WECode 2025 College Conference: Tech Fellowship Application
email body: Thanks for filling out Harvard WECode 2025 College Conference: Tech Fellowship Application Here's what was received. Harvard WECode 2025 College Conference: Tech Fellowship Application Thank you for your interest! The Harvard Women Engineers Code (WECode) Conference team is hosting our annual college women in technology conference on February 15-16 , 2025 at Harvard University. We are inviting current post-secondary students who identify as women/non-binary, with a demonstrated interest in technology, to apply to our Technology Fellowship! We will select a group of WECode Technology Fellows from across the country and world. If chosen, you will be a leader in the women in tech space, partnering with our Harvard student team to publicize the LARGEST student-run women in technology conference in the world via personal social media, digital communities/networks, and local outreach, and gain leadership experience in the women in tech space. Fellows will enjoy exclusive perks, including a free ticket to the conference, networking opportunities, and access to community resources. Please review this document for more information: https://tinyurl.com/wecodetechfellows25 This application is due November 3rd, 2024 at 11:59pm EST . Additionally, we will be hosting an informational meeting on Friday, October 18th, from 7:00 to 8:00pm EST . This is a great opportunity for students to learn more about the Tech Fellow program and ask any questions they may have. Please use this link to RSVP. There are THREE PORTIONS to this application : a mandatory application for WECode Technology Fellows, a mandatory committee selection (Professional Development, Digital Media, and Peer Engagement), and an optional application for a leadership role as a lead fellow for one of the committees listed above. Short Answer Questions: What experience do you have in technology (if none, what excites you about learning it)? What are you excited to do with technology in the future? (max 250 words) Why do you want to be a WECode Tech Fellow? What will you contribute to the Fellowship? (max 250 words) If chosen, how will you publicize WECode given the 3 areas above? (max 250 words) What skills, experiences, or qualities make you a good candidate for your top choice role? (max 250 words) BY APPLYING, you agree that you have read, understood, and agreed to carry out the responsibilities described in the Technology Fellowship Details document at https://tinyurl.com/wecodetechfellows25 We look forward to your application and hope to see you at Harvard WECode! Feel free to reach out to wecodepr@gmail.com with any questions (subject with “Tech Fellowship Program” in it!) This application is only for undergraduate students. Email * muskanmahajan2004@gmail.com WECode Fellowship Application: General Technology Fellow First Name * Muskan Last Name * Mahajan Phone Number 4708367544 Pronouns This fellowship is for students of minoritized gender identities! Please reach out if you have questions. ✓ she/her/hers they/them/theirs Other: Full Name of Post-Secondary Institution (School) -- please write the full name with appropriate capitalizations (Ex. Harvard University) * Georgia Tech City, State/Province -- please capitalize appropriately with no abbreviations! (Ex. Boston, Massachusetts) * Atlanta, Georgia Country * United States Current year in school * Must be a undergraduate post-secondary student. Enrolled students, students on gap years, and students on leaves of absences welcome! First-Year Second-Year Third-Year Fourth-Year Other: Were you a past Tech Fellow? If not, no worries! This will not impact your chance of being a Fellow for this year’s conference. * Yes No How did you find out about this opportunity? * ✓ Instagram Facebook Slack LinkedIn Reach-out from WECode Member Friend shared with me Teacher/School Counselor Parent Group RTC Other: What experience do you have in technology (if none, what excites you about learning it)? What are you excited to do with technology in the future? (max 250 words) * My advent into technology was through developing BELA (Bot for English Language Acquisition) - a full-stack language learning chatbot for Hindi-speaking students. I built BELA using Python's NLP libraries, such as NLTK and Transformers. BELA helped 35+ underserved students at an Indian non-profit I worked at improve their English skills through constant communication and fun, bite-sized exercises. The research for this prototype was published in EMNLP 2022, a moment that reinforced my passion for technology for social good. Since then, I’ve been building web projects for my community. One example is "Affirm," a GPT-3.5-based positive affirmations generator I made using Python and Flask. It accepts a user’s grievance as input and generates affirmations to help them cope better. My latest project is Buzz Bazaar, a GT-campus marketplace for second-hand goods. Since its release in May '24, it has helped 30 Yellow Jackets sell 45+ goods, make money and reduce waste. Building Buzz Bazaar taught me the value of iterative-development based on feedback and the skills to market my creation across campus. Finally, in future, I see myself develop solutions to ensure women's safety in Delhi, often dubbed India's "rape capital." This project would involve comprehensive research, leveraging the insights of survivors, policymakers, and medical professionals. My goal would be to create an accessible, frugal SOS system tailored for low-connectivity areas, empowering women with a reliable safety net that works within India’s unique socio-economic landscape. Why do you want to be a WECode Tech Fellow? What will you contribute to the Fellowship? (max 250 words) * A sophomore leading an interdisciplinary innovation club at her school, a senior developing an app to promote small businesses, and a junior with a tech-IG following of 25K (wink wink Skylar Basco).These are just some of the amazing women I met at Harvard WECode 2024. I want to be a WECode Tech Fellow so that I can surround myself with the incredible community of women it fosters and urge the women in my network to become a part of it too. As VP External at Georgia Tech's Women @ College of Computing club, I organize recruitment events for our network of over 650 women. Therefore, I know firsthand how impactful access to recruitment and professional development resources can be for young women in tech. Therefore, I’m eager to connect them to this unique opportunity. Finally, the professional perks of being a WECode Fellow — like coffee chats with companies like Notion and Five Rings LLC, and meeting other ambitious fellows across the country — appeal to me too. In terms of contribution, I am keen to join the Professional Development Committee. I’ve liaised with corporate sponsors like Bloomberg, Google, and Millennium in my current role at W@CC. Furthermore, as Event Director for a Women’s History Month panel discussion at "Startup Exchange" club, I have moderated discussions featuring senior leaders like Visa’s SWE Director. I’m excited to emulate these at WECode, helping to facilitate impactful discussions and expand the network of mentors and speakers available to the event. If chosen, how will you publicize WECode given the 3 areas above? (max 250 words) * personal social media, digital communities/networks, and local outreach As a tech fellow for Harvard WECode, I would leverage my extensive network and leadership positions to maximize publicity for the conference. For instance, as VP External of Georgia Tech's Women at College of Computing (650+ members) and Director of Events at Startup Exchange (350+ members), I have direct access to a large pool of potential attendees. I would promote WECode through our clubs' communication channels, including dedicated posts on our opportunities board on Slack and announcements during club meetings. My role in these organizations allows me to personally endorse WECode, adding credibility to the promotion. I'd also tap into my network of fellow CS majors - honestly majority of my friends and acquaintances here at Georgia Tech - particularly focusing on ambitious women in tech who are always seeking such opportunities. Beyond campus organizations, I organize regular internship application sprintathons in my campus apartment lounge. These events provide an ideal setting to introduce WECode to a diverse group of motivated students. I would encourage all participants to apply and consider attending the conference. Lastly, I'd utilize my LinkedIn network of 1800+ followers to spread the word about WECode, reaching a broader audience of tech enthusiasts and potential attendees beyond my immediate campus community. List specific communities/platforms, if any, that you are a part of, to which you can share WECode. * e.g. coding camps, Slack groups, Facebook groups, women in tech accounts, etc. Director of Events at Startup Exchange Georgia Tech, VP External at Women at College of Computing (W@CC) at GT, Member of Girls who code, Member of SWE Social media handle(s) * Please list the handle and the according social media app muskan_mjn (my IG), waccgt (w@cc's IG), startupexchangegt (SX GT) Link(s) to resume, LinkedIn, personal websites or portfolios, anything cool really :) optional! My resume: https://drive.google.com/file/d/15TQ3ljgCNOa1tNtMr33EACkgMyUiwvIG/view?usp=sharing Linkedin: https://www.linkedin.com/in/muskanmahajan/ The web app (buzz bazaar) I created last sem: buzzbazaar.app My product hunt page: https://www.producthunt.com/products/affirm-4 By electronically signing my name below, I agree that if I am selected to be a Tech Fellow, I have read the responsibilities described in the form description and will carry them out via outreach and pubbing. I understand that not following through (not pubbing, being uncommunicative, etc.) may have my free conference ticket and other ambassador perks revoked. * Muskan Mahajan Any other comments or questions? What schools do Tech fellows represent? Also, do we have agency over organizing our own initiatives WECode Committee Selection: General Member Upon acceptance into the WECode Tech Fellowship programs, all Tech Fellows must join one of three committees and attend its meetings. Description of Committees The three committees are: [ Professional Development ] Duties include: Facilitating Tech Fellow coffee chats Sourcing professional speakers and organizing a virtual speaker series Moderating workshops on professional development. [ Digital Media ] Duties include: Writing and editing guest blog posts featured on the WECode site Lead outreach to news sources for coverage of WECode 2023 Creating content for WECode’s official social media channels (IG/Tiktok) [ Peer Engagement ] Duties include: Leading fun socials and networking events Facilitating weekly discussions on relevant topics in tech Designing Tech Fellow merch Rank the committees from in order of preference (First choice = most preferred) * Professional Development Digital Media Peer Engagement First Choice Second Choice Third Choice WECode Fellowship Application: Lead Fellows The 6 chosen Lead Fellows must complete general Technology Fellowship responsibilities, in addition to taking on the responsibility of leading the 3 committees. What role are you applying for? Please rank in order of preference (1 = most preferred). If you are only interested in one position, leave "second choice" and "third choice" blank. Professional Development Lead Fellow Digital Media Lead Fellow Peer Engagement Lead Fellow First choice Second Choice Third Choice What skills, experiences, or qualities make you a good candidate for your top choice role? (max 250 words) * I am keen to join the Professional Development Committee. As VP External at Georgia Tech's Women at College of Computing Club, I’ve liaised with corporate sponsors like Bloomberg, Google, and Millennium. This experience has equipped me with the skills to reach out and establish connections with corporates and their representatives, and organize meaningful events with them. Furthermore, as Event Director for a Women’s History Month panel discussion at "Startup Exchange" club, I have organized and moderated discussions featuring senior leaders like Visa’s SWE Director and Forbes 30U30 Founder - after leading a cross functional team of 13. I’m excited to emulate this experience at WECode, helping to facilitate impactful discussions and expand the network of mentors and speakers available to the event. Any other comments or questions? Create your own Google Form Report Abuse

email subject: Thanks for applying for the Software Engineering Intern role with Boomi!
email body: Hi Muskan, Your application has been received for the Software Engineering Intern opportunity, and we're excited you're interested in joining the Boomi team! So what's next? 1) A member of the Hiring Team will review your resume and application. 2) If we'd like to move forward with your application, we'll be in touch to schedule a time to connect with you. If we determine it's a match for both of us after we connect, we'll reach out to schedule the next steps. This is typically an interview with the Hiring Manager but could include an assessment, or meeting with additional Boomi Team members you would collaborate with in this role. On average, a successful candidate can expect anywhere from 3-5 interviews before a decision is made. If we decide not to move forward with your candidacy at any point in the process, we'll let you know of our decision via phone or email. You've invested time in us, and deserve to be acknowledged! We'll also reach out regarding any other opportunities that we think may be a good fit. (You may opt out or request to remove your information from our database at any time.) Regards, Boomi Global Talent Acquisition ** Please note: Do not reply to this email. This email is sent from an unattended mailbox. Replies will not be read.

email subject: Your IBM Application: Next Steps
email body: Dear Muskan Mahajan, We are excited to see that you have applied for a position at IBM, and we want to ensure that you have the best opportunity to showcase your fantastic skills. We understand that resume alone doesn't always reflect a candidate's full potential. That's why we invite you to complete one or more of the following assessments, which will help us gain a more comprehensive view of your capabilities. IBM values accessibility and are committed to ensuring that every candidate has an equal opportunity to showcase their skills and potential. We support measures like additional time for persons with disabilities on selection assessments. We use following assessments for selection purposes. You will be invited to complete 1 or more of these assessments, depending on the role you are applying for. The next step in the process includes one or more assessments – described below. The Coding Assessment - helps us to understand your level of programming knowledge and ability. You will be presented with a coding interface to solve coding challenges. This is a timed assessment. We believe that these assessments will provide you with a better opportunity to showcase your skills, and we encourage you to take them seriously. We also want to make sure that you feel comfortable and supported throughout the process. All applicants are requested to click the accommodation link below. If you are a person with a disability, please follow the link to submit any adjustments that you require, such as extra time. IBM will review the details of your requirement and work with you on any adjustment options for your application. It is important that you submit your requirements before starting any assessments. If you do not need extra time on the assessments, please mark your response in the link below. Accommodation Form Please note that this form must be completed for each position you apply for that requires an assessment. For additional information and helpful tips, please visit our blog We appreciate your interest in joining our team and wish you the best of luck as you complete these assessments. We can't wait to see all that you have to offer! Sincerely, The IBM Talent Acquisition Team 727366BR Software Engineer - AI-powered Automation Intern: 2025

email subject: Blackstone Application – Invitation to pymetrics Digital Interview Assessment
email body: Hello, This is a reminder that you have been invited to complete the next step of our application process where we will be leveraging the Pymetrics one-way digital interview platform. Please complete this portion of the applications process as soon as you are able. Instructions: Please click the following link to complete the pymetrics assessment: https://www.pymetrics.com/invite/sc.977b6d9a7f3d41f5a42d20f2e8e9d251/ 1. Register for a Pymetrics account (please be sure to use the same email address that you received this invitation to). 2. If using a smartphone, you will be directed to the App store. Download the app and then come back to link above. 3. Record your interview responses. Please Note: Pymetrics digital interviewing is supported on the following web browsers: Chrome, Firefox, and Microsoft Edge. On mobile, you must be on a minimum of iOS11 for Apple devices or 4.4 on Android devices. Pymetrics is not compatible with tablet devices. Next Steps: Once you have completed your interview, our recruiting team will review your responses and will be in touch with next steps. More information on the Pymetrics Digital Interview: The digital interview helps us learn more about your prior experiences and your interest in the role. This part will take an additional 20 minutes. You will be asked to record your responses to five interview questions. The video interview does not provide disability accommodations at this time. Please e-mail campusrecruiting@blackstone.com for further assistance. If you have any technical questions about completing Pymetrics, please reach out to support@pymetrics.com for help. Best, Blackstone Campus Recruiting Team Privacy Notice: Blackstone invites candidates who have applied to campus programs to submit voluntarily video recordings in which they provide answers to questions provided. If you choose to submit your recording, we will process your name, contact information, video and responses to the questions to help us shortlist and select candidates, provide mentoring services and conduct talent assessments. Your video recording will be stored by our vendor Pymetrics in the U.S. and will be accessed by Blackstone hiring managers. The video recording will be deleted after the evaluation process has been completed, unless further storage is required by applicable law. For more information about our data practices and your privacy rights, see our privacy notice at www.blackstone.com/privacy. Candidates who prefer to provide answers to the questions using a different format may contact campusrecruiting@blackstone.com and we will discuss an alternative solution. Tips & Tricks for a Successful Video Interview DO your homework, you have a limited amount of time to convey your knowledge, research current deals and initiatives ahead of time DO treat this like an in-person interview, dress in business attire DO set up a tidy and quiet space to conduct the interview. While you are being evaluated on what you say keep in mind the reviewers can view your background DO pay attention to your lighting, avoid sitting in front of a sunlit window and try not to use overhead lighting DO test your technology ahead of time, make sure your camera, sound, and internet are all working DON'T use any examples in your answers that involve any illegal or illicit topics DON'T share the interview questions with friends or classmates, we want everyone to have an even playing field while completing DON'T read from notes, the moving of your eyes from reading can distract the reviewer. Instead, practice your answers ahead of time so you sound confident and relaxed

email subject: You have successfully submitted your IBM job application.
email body: IBM Careers Thank you for applying Muskan Mahajan, thank you for applying to the role of Software Developer Intern Ref:726891BR at IBM. We’re excited that you’re considering us as your next employer! Here at IBM, we believe our greatest asset is the IBMer. We strive every day to foster a culture of conscious inclusion for all individuals and provide IBMers the opportunity to make a positive impact on the world while bringing their authentic selves to work. To that end, we want to be as transparent as possible with you about what to expect next now that you’ve applied to IBM. Currently, your application is being reviewed by real IBMers, who are experts in screening resumes in their respective fields. If there's a potential match, we’ll contact you to discuss the next steps of our hiring process. While you wait to hear from us: • Visit our special careers page to find tips on acing your interview and career advice from current IBMers. You can also check out our application process page to learn more about how we hire at IBM. • Connect with us on our Life@IBM social media channels (links in the footer below) where you can engage with us further, discover what life at IBM is like, and see how IBMers around the world are making an impact. You can also check the status of your application at any time by visiting your IBM Career Portal . If you have any questions, please feel free to send us a direct message on any of our social channels. Thank you again, Muskan, for taking the time to apply to IBM and for your interest in becoming a future IBMer. Best regards, Your IBM Recruiting Team ibm.com/jobs © IBM | Data Privacy Policy To ensure delivery to your inbox, please add talent@ibm.com to your address book. Please do not reply to this email, as we are unable to respond from this address. © IBM Corporation 2023. email subject: Complete Your Netflix Software Engineering Internship Application | Next Steps
email body: Hi Muskan , Thank you for your interest in our Netflix Software Engineering Internship role! In order for your application to be reviewed, please complete this Airtable form . Your application will only be considered complete after you submit this form in conjunction with the application you already submitted on our Netflix Careers site. Please only complete the form once; duplicate submissions will not be considered. Due to the large volume of applications we receive, we're sorry that we're unable to personally follow up with each applicant. Our full recruiting process may take several weeks, so we kindly ask for your patience as we complete candidate reviews and interviews. In order to maintain a fair and equitable hiring process, we will not be able to accommodate very tight deadlines. For applicants selected to proceed, the interview process will begin with a CodeSignal Assessment. The results from this assessment will be used as just one additional data point to determine who will be invited to the interview rounds. The first two rounds of interviews are technical/coding interviews with Netflix software engineers, and the final round consists of both technical and behavioral questions. Your advancement will be based on the feedback at each round. Important Note: If you're selected to move forward, the next email you receive will come from CodeSignal; we strongly recommend adding no-reply@codesignal.com to your contacts to prevent spam filtering. Our goal is to reach out to candidates who are chosen for initial next steps within the next two to three weeks. If you haven’t heard from us by then, we may have reached interview capacity. Note that our Software Engineering intern interview process is designed to assess your generalist skills, coding fundamentals, and aptitude. Offers will be extended to join our 2025 Intern class at Netflix, where we’ll have 3 start date options in Summer 2025 to centralize onboarding programming and training. Thanks again, and good luck! -The Netflix Emerging Talent Team ﻿ Please note that this email address is not monitored and replies to this message will not be read. You received this email because you've applied, been referred, attended a event, or expressed interest in working at Netflix. This email was sent to muskanmahajan2004@gmail.com by Netflix, Los Gatos,CA,USA. Unsubscribe

email subject: [Reminder] Jamboard application wind down
email body: The Jamboard application will no longer be available starting October 1, 2024 Dear Jamboard user, This is a reminder that we will wind down the Jamboard app starting October 1, 2024. Between October 1, 2024 and December 31, 2024 , the app will be placed in “view-only” mode and you’ll no longer be able to create new or edit existing Jams on any platform, including the web, iOS, and Android platforms. During this time you can continue to back up your Jam files. What do you need to do? Our records show that you have recently used the Jamboard app or have at least 1 Jam in your Google Drive. We recommend backing up your Jam files by exporting them to PDF or migrating them to one of our partners. Learn more about our partners below and how you can import your Jams to continue working on your whiteboards. FigJam by Figma Lucidspark by Lucid Software Miro On December 31, 2024 , we will complete the wind down of the Jamboard application and you will no longer be able to access your Jam files. We’re here to help For more information, you can visit our FAQ page . Thanks for choosing Google Workspace. – The Google Workspace Team Was this information helpful? © 2024 Google LLC 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043 You have received this mandatory email announcement to update you about important information related to your Google account.

email subject: Inviting Application from School Student Volunteers
email body: Your students want to build a better world. And we want to help! Pramerica Life Insurance Emerging Visionaries is a national recognition program that awards student volunteers for their innovative solutions to financial and societal challenges in their communities. It is the evolution of the Pramerica Spirit of Community Awards which has honored thousands of young people during its 13-year history in India and over 27-year-old legacy in the United States. We continue to identify, celebrate and support the next generation of visionaries. Driven by Purpose. At Pramerica Life Insurance, we make lives better by solving the financial challenges of our changing world. And because we believe those solutions can come from anywhere, the more people know about Emerging Visionaries; the more impactful our work can be. So, as a progressive school that encourages students to do better for their communities and find solutions to challenges, we look forward to your participation. Help Students Apply for Pramerica Life Insurance Emerging Visionaries. Applications are open till February 18, 2024 for students of classes 8 th to 12 th . 2 national honorees will be selected to represent India at the international award ceremony in the United States* They will also qualify to receive INR 50,000 as prize money and gold medals. 23 finalists will be awarded silver medals and certificates for their dedication and commitment to their communities. Reach out to us to organise an implementation and information workshop. +91 8585 925927 # contact@emergingvisionaries.com www.emergingvisionaries.com This email was sent to muskanmahajan2004@gmail.com why did I get this? unsubscribe from this list update subscription preferences Pramerica Emerging Visionaries · New Delhi · Delhi, Delhi 110085 · India

email subject: [Action Advised] Jamboard application wind down
email body: The Jamboard application will be no longer be available starting October 1, 2024. Dear Jamboard user, We’re writing to let you know that we will wind down the Jamboard app next year, and offer integrations with industry-leading third-party whiteboard tools FigJam , Lucidspark , and Miro as alternatives for whiteboarding in Google Workspace. These popular tools have numerous advanced features that empower users to collaborate seamlessly together inside of Google Workspace. Starting October 1, 2024 , you’ll no longer be able to create new or edit existing Jams on any platform, including the web, iOS, and Android. Between October 1, 2024 and December 31, 2024, the app will be placed in “view-only” mode, during which time you can continue to back up your Jam files. Learn more . What do you need to do? Our records show that you have recently used the Jamboard app or have at least 1 Jam in your Google Drive. On December 31, 2024 , we will wind down the Jamboard application and you will no longer be able to access your Jam files. We recommend you evaluate our multiple whiteboard partners, which provide numerous advanced features that empower you to collaborate seamlessly inside of Google Workspace. FigJam by Figma Lucidspark by Lucid Software Miro In the coming months, we’ll provide you paths to retain your Jamboard data or migrate it to FigJam, Lucidspark, and Miro within just a few clicks, well before the Jamboard app winds down in late 2024. email subject: Applying for a specific role?
email body: Applying for a specific role? Ask yourself these 5 questions first: ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ Forwarded this email? Subscribe here for more Applying for a specific role? Ask yourself these 5 questions first: Kareem Abukhadra Sep 15 READ IN APP 1) Is the role actively being hired for? You want to find roles and titles that are actively being hired for, a lot. The more jobs available, the more you can apply to. And that means you can land more interviews, receive more offers, and have more freedom. 2) Do the role's responsibilities align with my past experience? Your past experience and expertise should lend themselves to the responsibilities of the role you’re applying for. Although they may not line up completely, a correlation is needed. 3) Can I tailor my resume to display my competence for the role? This is the key to landing multiple offers. You want to write your resume to make it line up with the responsibilities of the role you’re applying for. Again, although they may not line up completely, it’s important to cater past experiences (without lying or embellishing) to include the parts most relevant to the recruiter or hiring manager. 4) Are the role's responsibilities uniform across companies? This point is key to landing multiple offers. It’ll let you apply to each job with the same resume, and increase efficiency in the application process — while improving your chances of landing multiple interviews. 5) Does the role allow me to drive quantifiable value for the company? When you’re able to drive (and communicate that you can drive) quantifiable value for a company, your leverage in negotiation increases exponentially. Companies don’t hire out of the goodness of their heart. They hire to solve a problem, or make more money. Communicating that you accomplish one or both of those missions for them, and putting a number on it is crucial. As a general rule of thumb, you want to ask for ~20% of the value you’ll drive. But, as always, that number changes with leverage. Check out this post for more info on how to accomplish this. The point is this… Your answer needs to be "yes" to all of these questions. This'll let you apply to multiple jobs, land multiple interviews, and negotiate with higher leverage. Any questions? Reply with them! If you liked this post and want personalized coaching for your job search, why not join our accelerator Relentless? email subject: New course with Google Cloud: Understanding and Applying Text Embeddings with Vertex AI
email body: New course with Google Cloud: Understanding and Applying Text Embeddings with Vertex AI Learn the fundamentals of text embeddings Dear Muskan, Introducing a new short course made in collaboration with Google Cloud: Understanding and Applying Text Embeddings with Vertex AI . Text embeddings, which are numerical representations of text, play a significant role in various tasks involving the identification of similar items, like Google searches, online shopping recommendations, and personalized music suggestions. With this course, you’ll harness the capabilities of Google Cloud’s Vertex AI API to generate text embeddings for tasks like classification, outlier detection, text clustering, and semantic search. Upon finishing the course, you’ll acquire the skills to: Use text embeddings to capture the meaning of sentences and paragraphs Use the ScaNN (Scalable Nearest Neighbors) library for efficient semantic search Combine text generation from an LLM with semantic search to build a question-answering system Start integrating text embeddings into LLM applications today! email subject: 📈 Master Data Science with a PG Diploma in Applied Statistics
email body: Build a successful career in data science by working with real-world data sets By joining the Postgraduate Diploma in Applied Statistics , you will learn how to analyse, visualise, and present large data sets. You will benefit from a 360-degree view into how official data systems are built, develop experience with data analysis tools in popular coding platforms like Python and R, and acquire skills to build, interpret, and improve official databases. How will the PG Diploma in Applied Statistics from ISI benefit you? Learn from the Institution that works with the government and trains key officers of the Ministry Prepare for the real-world by working with data from large government and international projects Interact in live sessions with renowned, globally-recognised faculty Develop industry-ready skills and learn from accomplished experts Receive career readiness support via industry sessions, mentorship from experts and networking opportunities Gain access to an exclusive student community and alumni network Access potential job opportunities facilitated by ISI via the placement committee. Placements are a student-driven activity - there is no placement guarantee offered by ISI. The deadline to apply has been extended until 16 July 2023. Learn more Have questions? email subject: Mehak Mahajan - M&A Analyst Application
email body: Dear Team Junior IB, I hope you are doing well. I am Mehak, a first-year BSc Economics student at King's College London . I am writing to apply for the M&A Analyst position at Junior IB. I've included here my CV, which provides a comprehensive overview of my academic and professional background. In my first year of university, I have been fortunate to get exposure to the financial industry by securing five finance spring week offers. I have also attached a sample report I recently wrote on Johnson & Johnson's acquisition of Abiomed . It reflects my understanding of the M&A landscape and showcases my writing skills. I hope you find it informative and insightful. I have been following Junior IB's work closely, and I am impressed by the exceptional quality of your publication. The depth of analysis, industry insights, and comprehensive coverage of M&A transactions have consistently caught my attention. Joining Junior IB would provide me with an invaluable opportunity to contribute to the M&A field while learning from like-minded peers. In addition, my enthusiasm, commitment, and strong work ethic will enable me to contribute meaningfully to your team and support the publication's mission. Once again, I sincerely appreciate your time and consideration. I look forward to the possibility of joining Junior IB and contributing to your team's success! Yours sincerely, Mehak Mahajan

email subject: Reminder: 5/22 Application Deadline for 2023 Interstellar Initiative
email body: Reminder: 5/22 Application Deadline for 2023 Interstellar Initiative Boost your career with this prestigious opportunity. Dear Colleague: I'm writing to remind you that we are inviting applications for the 2023 Interstellar Initiative through Tuesday, May 22, 2023. Presented by the Japan Agency for Medical Research and Development (AMED) and the New York Academy of Sciences (NYAS), this prestigious program takes place in New York City this fall, from September 13-15th. Selected scientists will participate in the 3-day in-person workshop , with travel expenses covered by AMED. The Interstellar Initiative builds international and interdisciplinary research collaborations between Early Career Investigators (ECIs) with the end goal of addressing challenges in basic science. Guided by mentors and supported by modest funding from AMED, teams will be established to develop proposals for international funding agencies. Learn More & Apply Here are the eligibility requirements for the Interstellar Initiative: Doctoral degree awarded no earlier than 2013 and ten years or less of active research experience. An independent, tenure-track position or an equivalent title at a university, private research institution, academic medical center, or government laboratory. Proficiency in spoken and written English for the purpose of professional science communication. A background in one of the four broad categories of biomedical sciences, life sciences, physical/natural sciences, and biotechnology/analytical technology. Is the Interstellar Initiative for you? If you want to grow professionally by working with a group of exceptionally talented cross-disciplinary early-career researchers from around the globe, under the mentorship of esteemed senior scientists, then the Interstellar Initiative is for you! Apply by May 22nd I hope to see your application for this career-boosting program by May 22nd! And please share this email with your early-career colleagues who may also be interested in applying. Thank you. Sincerely, Megan Prescott, PhD Program Manager New York Academy of Sciences Questions? Feel free to reach out to us at interstellar@nyas.org . Plug into the World’s Smartest Network©. Join the Academy. Copyright © 2023 New York Academy of Sciences, All rights reserved. You are receiving this email because you opted in to receive email updates from the New York Academy of Sciences. Our mailing address is: New York Academy of Sciences 115 Broadway 8th Floor New York , NY 10006 Add us to your address book Want to change how you receive these emails? You can update your preferences or unsubscribe from this list .

Next Steps: Complete HackerRank Test To complete the application process, you will need to complete a HackerRank assignment. We will send you the assessment within the next 24 hours . HackerRank Assessment Deadline: May 14th All admission decisions will be communicated no later than May 23rd, so please keep that in mind when planning your application timeline. All the best, Team at CodePath

email subject: Closing today: Applications for PG Diploma in Applied Statistics
email body: Submit your application before the final deadline In the Postgraduate Diploma in Applied Statistics , you will learn data analytics skills, develop an ability to distill information and clearly articulate your findings. You will also establish a solid foundation in applied statistics and learn the rigorous principles that guide statistical inference. What makes the PG Diploma in Applied Statistics special? Learn with real data from large government projects: Work with open databases used in policy and decision-making in public and private sectors. Gain expertise with specialized tracks: Choose between two specializations of Official Statistics or Data Analytics depending on your interest. Learn how to analyze, visualize, and present large data sets: The programme is built around official data systems, and you’ll benefit from a 360-degree view into how these systems are built and used. Interact with and learn from globally recognised faculty: You will learn from the same faculty who teach the highly rigorous campus programmes at ISI and are also regularly engaged in the training of officers of the Indian Statistical Service. Final deadline to submit your application is today. Classes are starting on 9 Mar 2023 . Submit now Have questions?
