email subject: Closing in 2 weeks: Applications for PG Diploma in Applied Statistics
email body: Submit your application before the deadline In the Postgraduate Diploma in Applied Statistics , you will learn data analytics skills, develop an ability to distill information and clearly articulate your findings. You will also establish a solid foundation in applied statistics and learn the rigorous principles that guide statistical inference. What makes the PG Diploma in Applied Statistics special? Learn with real data from large government projects: Work with open databases used in policy and decision-making in public and private sectors. Gain expertise with specialized tracks: Choose between two specializations of Official Statistics or Data Analytics depending on your interest. Learn how to analyze, visualize, and present large data sets: The programme is built around official data systems, and you’ll benefit from a 360-degree view into how these systems are built and used. Interact with and learn from globally recognised faculty: You will learn from the same faculty who teach the highly rigorous campus programmes at ISI and are also regularly engaged in the training of officers of the Indian Statistical Service. To get an early decision, submit your application before 15 Feb 2023 . Apply now Have questions? Schedule a call with our admissions counsellor. email subject: Application for Consumer/Retail Analyst Role - Mehak Mahajan (Updated CV)
email body: Dear Sir/Madam, I am a first-year BSc Economics student at King's College London, and I would like to express my interest in obtaining a place as a Consumer/Retail Analyst at ODT Capital. My decision to apply for this role stems from my passion for investment and my aim to use my research skills to develop investment recommendations for a student-led investment fund. To develop the fundamentals of finance in high school, I undertook a virtual training programme by the Indian Business School, namely ‘Trading Basics’, through which I learnt how to analyse the corporate financial statements of a company to conduct its fundamental analysis. I completed a 1-month accounting and financial planning internship to apply this knowledge practically. Here, I prepared the ratio analysis reports of 4 major fast-moving consumer goods companies, enhancing my analytical skills. I also understood how to prepare a client’s financial plan based on their financial goals, risk appetite and financial position. At university, I participated in a trading simulation, where I built an ESG portfolio that beat the S&P500 index by 25%. During the spring break, I will complete the 12-week Investment Insight Programme at the Girls Are Investors Organisation to develop my investment skills further. I am also currently preparing for the CFA Level 1 exam. I believe that my team-building skills, communication and research competency, and ability to lead initiatives will add value to the team at ODT Capital: 1. Team player: Volunteering as an Events Associate at the King's College in London Women in Business Society and a Leadership Trainer at Girls in Charge has enabled me to work as a team player and leader. I have also previously been chosen to attend Harvard University's competitive Youth Lead Change programme, where I led a team of 5 students to pitch a hypothetical social initiative on sustainable farming. 2. Communication: Leading pro-bono projects at King's Junior Consulting Group has aided my ability to follow up with my team and the client, ensuring their needs are met. Previously, I have also represented my school at various MUNs, Youth Parliaments, debate platforms, and the ‘World Scholar Cup’, where my team was chosen for the global round in Singapore. 3. Research and Writing: My interest in research and writing has led me to opportunities like working at the Sri Ram College of Commerce for their elite Research Writing Programme, writing articles as an incoming Junior Writer at King's Business review and even starting my blog, Money Mind Media, where I conduct research and publish reports on topics of socio-economic and financial importance. 4. Entrepreneurship: I have also served as the Founder and President of my school's Business Club, the first-ever student club of my school, where I single-handedly built a team of 10 students and a membership of 70+ students. Some of our events: SVIS Business Conclave (150+ participants; distributed prices worth INR 10K), Webinar on Financial Literacy for Teens (60+ students), Walk-a-Thon Fundraiser (INR 30K raised). I am attaching my CV for your perusal. Again, thank you for considering my application, and I look forward to hearing back from you. Kind regards, Mehak Mahajan

email subject: Application for Consumer/Retail Analyst Role - Mehak Mahajan (Updated CV)
email body: Dear Sir/Madam, I am a first-year BSc Economics student at King's College London, and I would like to express my interest in obtaining a place as a Consumer/Retail Analyst at ODT Capital. My decision to apply for this role stems from my passion for investment and my aim to use my research skills to develop investment recommendations for a student-led investment fund. To develop the fundamentals of finance, I undertook a virtual training programme in high school, namely ‘Trading Basics’ by the Indian Business School, in which I learnt to analyse the corporate financial statements of a company to conduct its fundamental analysis. To practically apply this knowledge, I completed an accounting and financial planning internship, where I prepared the ratio analysis reports of 4 major fast-moving consumer goods companies, enhancing my analytical skills. I also understood how to prepare a client’s financial plan based on their financial goals, risk appetite and financial position. At university, I participated in a trading simulation, where I built an ESG portfolio that beat the S&P500 index by 25%. To develop my investment skills further, I will complete a 12-week Investment Insight Programme at the Girls Are Investors Organisation, and I am currently preparing for CFA Level 1. I believe that my team-building skills, communication and research competency, and ability to lead initiatives will add value to the team at ODT Capital: 1. Team player: Volunteering as an Events Associate at the King's College in London Women in Business Society and a Leadership Trainer at Girls in Charge has aided my ability to work as a team player and leader. I have also previously been chosen to attend Harvard University's competitive Youth Lead Change programme, where I led a team of 5 students to pitch a hypothetical social initiative on sustainable farming. 2. Communication: Leading pro-bono projects at King's Junior Consulting Group has aided my ability to follow up with my team and the client, ensuring their needs are met. Previously, I have also represented my school at various MUNs, Youth Parliaments, debate platforms, and the ‘World Scholar Cup’, where my team was chosen for the global round in Singapore. 3. Research and Writing: My interest in research and writing has led me to opportunities like working at the Sri Ram College of Commerce for their elite Research Writing Programme, writing articles as an incoming Junior Writer at King's Business review and even starting my blog, Money Mind Media, where I conduct research and publish reports on topics of socio-economic and financial importance. 4. Entrepreneurship: I have also served as the Founder and President of my school's Business Club, the first-ever student club of my school, where I single-handedly built a team of 10 students and a membership of 70+ students. Some of our events: SVIS Business Conclave (150+ participants; distributed prices worth INR 10K), Webinar on Financial Literacy for Teens (60+ students), Walk-a-Thon Fundraiser (INR 30K raised). I am attaching my CV for your perusal. Thank you for considering my application, and I look forward to hearing back from you. Kind regards, Mehak Mahajan

email subject: Earn a postgraduate diploma and build skills for a career in applied statistics
email body: Interact with and learn from globally recognised faculty The Indian Statistical Institute (ISI) functions under the Ministry of Statistics and Programme Implementation (MOSPI) of the Government of India. In the Postgraduate Diploma in Applied Statistics , you will learn from the same faculty who teach the highly rigorous campus programmes at ISI. You will also have the opportunity to learn from experts who handle large data sets to facilitate policy decisions. The regular and guest faculty members, in addition to their teaching and research activities, are also regularly engaged in the training of officers of the Indian Statistical Service. Applications for Spring 2023 cohort are closing soon! Classes starting in March 2023. Apply now Have questions? Please do not hesitate to get in touch by emailing us at pgdas.support@isical.ac.in About Indian Statistical Institute ISI functions under the Ministry of Statistics and Programme Implementation (MOSPI) of the Government of India and is involved in high impact projects involving large data and also trains the key officers of the ministry. ISI Kolkata has more than 250 faculty members who have achieved excellence in their research work. The contribution of the faculty has been recognized frequently with awards such as the Padma Shri Award, S. S. Bhatnagar Award, Fellowship of Indian Academy of Science to name a few. 18 scientists from ISI Kolkata got featured among the top 2% scientists in a global list compiled by the prestigious Stanford University in October 2021. email subject: Investment Banking Internship Application - Mehak Mahajan
email body: Dear Sir/Madam, I am a first-year Economics BSc student at King's College London , and I would like to express my interest in obtaining a place as an Investment Banking Intern at Silver Mile Capital. I aspire to pursue a career in investment banking because I think it is a challenging, fascinating, and fast-growing sector that will enable me to combine my computational and analytical backgrounds while creating a meaningful, tangible impact on other actors in the economy, like small businesses, social enterprises and large corporations. In addition, Investment banking offers a fast-paced environment where there is always something new to learn, new developments that affect your work, and opportunities to interact with diverse clients, interact with bright individuals and gain exposure to high-profile transitions. I am confident that the skills and competencies I have developed throughout my studies and extracurricular activities make me a suitable candidate. As a board member or associate, my involvement in various student societies has enabled me to cultivate my teamwork and leadership skills. I am a Consultant at King's Junior Consulting, an Events Associate at the KCL Women in Business Society and a Leadership Trainer at the nationwide Girls In Charge Initiative. Simultaneously, I have volunteered for organisations like WISH charity and Udayan Care as a Fundraising Volunteer and English Language Tutor , respectively. Since high school, I have always been interested in analysing diverse financial topics and the critical M&A transactions happening globally. This interest in research and writing has led me to gain opportunities like working at the Sri Ram College of Commerce for their elite research writing programme and even starting my blog, Money Mind Media , where I publish reports on socio-economic and financial importance. Additionally, I have served as the Founder and President of my school's Business Club , the first-ever student club of my school, where I single-handedly built a team of 10 students and a membership of 70+ students . I have also gained practical knowledge and experience in the financial industry by completing two internships in accounting and financial planning and attending financial modelling boot camps, company insight events and virtual training programmes. Participating in these activities has enabled me to stay organised, manage my time, think constructively and communicate my ideas effectively. My interest in Silver Mile Capital stems from the fact that it is a specialised investment bank and the company's culture and values. After researching the company, I found out that Silver Mile puts a strong emphasis on offering employees a supportive environment where they can challenge themselves to tackle complex financial problems and make a meaningful impact. I am sure that an internship at Silver Mile Capital will offer me an excellent opportunity to gain invaluable knowledge of how investment banking operates, as well as the chance to apply my knowledge in practice and add more pieces to the puzzle of my understanding of this fascinating field. In addition, experiencing the work and culture of the company and gaining exposure to business while networking with professionals and students interested in investment banking is a great way to deepen my understanding of the sector. Therefore, I am attaching my CV for your perusal. Thank you for considering my application, and I am excited to hear from you. Kind regards, Mehak Mahajan

email subject: Closing today: Priority applications for PG Diploma in Applied Statistics
email body: Submit your application before the deadline In the Postgraduate Diploma in Applied Statistics , you will learn data analytics skills, develop an ability to distill information and clearly articulate your findings. You will also establish a solid foundation in applied statistics and learn the rigorous principles that guide statistical inference. What makes the PG Diploma in Applied Statistics special? Learn with real data from large government projects: Work with open databases used in policy and decision-making in public and private sectors. Gain expertise with specialized tracks: Choose between two specializations of Official Statistics or Data Analytics depending on your interest. Learn how to analyze, visualize, and present large data sets: The programme is built around official data systems, and you’ll benefit from a 360-degree view into how these systems are built and used. Interact with and learn from globally recognised faculty: You will learn from the same faculty who teach the highly rigorous campus programmes at ISI and are also regularly engaged in the training of officers of the Indian Statistical Service. Priority application deadline is today! Apply now Have questions? email subject: Application deadline this Friday! | Global Management Programme in Operations and Supply Chain
email body: Watch this video of Introduction to Sustainable Operations and Supply Chain The world is facing two significant problems: Climate change and loss of biodiversity . In recent years, companies have been facing increasing pressure from activists, investors, and customers, to reduce the environmental impacts of their operations and supply chains. Companies have been responding to this with innovative products and services that are based on cradle-to-cradle blueprints and designs for the environment (DOE) . Many enterprises worldwide are embarking on “ circular economy models ” to create “ closed-loop supply chains ”. Developing circular economy models, sustainability is becoming more critical in all functional business areas such as procurement, production, packaging, physical distribution, and reverse logistics. Learn more with the Global Management Programme in Operations and Supply Chain from ISB. Application deadline is on December 30th, 2022 . If you have any questions about admissions, please email asis_sidhu@isb.edu. Learn more Curious to know more? Watch this webinar recording to learn more about this programme from the faculty at Indian School of Business. Watch now About Indian School of Business Ranked #1 in India by Financial Times World MBA Rankings 2022 Triple accredition Accreditations from AMBA, EFMD Quality Improvement System (EQUIS), and the Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of Business (AACSB). International Exposure ISB’s curriculum has been carefully set up to give its students the ability to get international exposure at various levels. email subject: Applications open for PG Diploma in Applied Statistics
email body: Apply now and build a career in applied statistics Applications for the Postgraduate Diploma in Applied Statistics from the Indian Statistical Institute are now open ! This programme emphasizes on the use of real-world data, including data from governments and international organizations that are available in the public domain. You will gain the necessary background for collection, visualization, and analysis of data for solving real problems. You will learn to build, maintain, and interpret official databases used for policy and decision making. By taking up this PG Diploma, you will get to: Learn how to analyze, visualize, and present large data sets Learn fundamentals and then choose your specialization Learn with open databases used in public and private projects Applications open! Classes starting March 2023. Learn more Have questions? He will outline the core components of the FastAPI web framework, and his application will leverage the newly-released Stable Diffusion text-to-image, deep learning model. Learners who want to build AI applications with FastAPI Learners who want to understand FastAPI’s architecture Learners who are interested in Python API web framework Those with a non-technical background are welcome to attend. email subject: [Upcoming Event] Branching out of the Notebook: ML Application Development with GitHub
email body: [Upcoming Event] Branching out of the Notebook: ML Application Development with GitHub Dear Muskan, Join us for a live, interactive workshop that teaches you how to use code from an existing containerized ML web application to deploy a new open-source text-to-image diffusion model for internal stakeholders. This hands-on session will cover how to accomplish this task using version control best practices, including GitHub branch development and pull requests. MacOS will be used for the demo, and all setup and deployment codes will be provided. Those with a non-technical background are welcome to attend. Special thanks to FourthBrain for co-hosting the event with us! Can't attend live? Don't worry. For anyone registered, we will be sending out the recorded sessions afterward. Don't miss out! Tune in at 9 AM PST on Wednesday, Nov. 9 Register Now We have more events coming up. Go ahead, check them out! Pie & AI events November 2: USA Pennsylvania - Data in the Cloud More upcoming events The DeepLearning.AI Team You've received this email because you are signed up to receive event updates from DeepLearning.AI DeepLearning.AI, 195 Page Mill Road, Suite 115, Palo Alto, CA 94306, United States Unsubscribe Manage preferences

email body: Join us on Tuesday, November 15, 2022 ... ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ ͏‌ Bachelor of Applied Arts and Sciences The University of North Texas (UNT)’s Bachelor of Applied Arts and Sciences (B.A.A.S.) degree has been named one of America’s 100 Best College Buys® for 24 consecutive years. Alumni of the on-campus B.A.A.S. have gone on to hold management and specialist positions in sectors like banking, education, retail and more while others go on to attend graduate school. Students in the B.A.A.S. bachelor’s completion degree receive the same high-quality instruction as on-campus students and earn the same degree while learning when and where it works best for them. The next deadline is: Friday, November 18 Get started UNT B.A.A.S. on Coursera: Program Overview Join Heather Treadway, Ana White, Stephanie Myers, and Indra Bhagat from UNT New College Advising and the Office of Digital Strategy and Innovation as they outline the Bachelor of Applied Arts and Sciences program. The webinar will cover B.A.A.S. concentration options, core requirements, flexibility and transferability of coursework and more. There will also be a Q&A at the end of the webinar. email body: 🆘🎓 Muskan, looking for help with your university application? email subject: Submit your application for review by a former admissions officer!
email body: Hello! Hope you are doing well! Ben will be meeting with former MIT and Cornell admissions officer Angela Conley on October 24th and 25th to go over our students' applications for EA/ED. You just have to submit your application in time for review. The link is here: https://ivyachievement.formstack.com/forms/reviewupload Please submit by 10PM your local time on Saturday, October 22nd! (Angela needs some time to review before meeting with Ben.) You will get feedback on: 1. Academics and test scores 2. Extracurricular activities 3. Essays 4. Letters of recommendation (if available) 5. Any "red flags" identified You should upload as much as you can to simulate the real admissions process . This means a PDF of your Common App, transcripts, score reports (even if self-reporting), resume/CV (if submitting), all LORs that you have, and anything else you might be submitting to colleges. In addition to your Common App, you may submit up to two supplements . Files are stored securely. Please refer to the attached formatting and writing guide to finalize your essays and remainder of your application for submission. Pay special attention to the sections on line spacing and capitalization ; they can help you avoid common mistakes. If you don't yet have a PDF of your Common App or have made changes since your last submission, select any school you haven't applied to yet (and whose application is complete) and click " Review and Submit - Common App, " then click " Review and Submit ." Don't worry - this will not actually submit your Common App. You'll then be able to right-click on the PDF that pops up and save it to your computer. Please let us know if there's anything we can help with! The IvyAchievement Team

email subject: Muskan make your Ivy league application stand out
email body: Free Writing Course Free Writing Program for High School Students ­ ­ ­ ­ ­ High School Writing Program ­ ­ ­ ­ ­ Hey Muskan, ­ ­ ­ ­ ­ Did you know?? Universities such as Harvard, Stanford, MIT & other Ivy league schools have an acceptance rate of only 5%. ­ ­ We all know that schools can only accommodate a certain number of students every year. Within these applicants you have "athletes," "legacy students" (those with relatives who attended the university), “dean's interest list,” “children of the faculty,” etc. and if you do not belong to any of these groups you are already behind. Roughly 60,000 applications are received by Ivy League Schools every year. How do you make your application stand out? With your ability to write excellent essays Why take a chance with your future especially for a skill you can ace? Become a better writer today. email subject: 5 ways to get ahead of the US application process!
email body: 5 ways to get ahead of the US application process! You are 45 days away from the first US Early Application deadline. Here are 5 things you must complete now. Dear Vikas, You are 45 days away from the first US Early Application deadline! Here are 5 things you must complete now: 1. Finalise your list of Early Action/Early Decision colleges You must identify your best-fit colleges and apply early to optimise your chances. 2. Engage with colleges on your list Attend admissions sessions, embark on virtual tours, register for interviews and connect with colleges, their faculty and alums via their social media pages. Doing so will enable you to demonstrate interest and assimilate content for supplementary essays. 3. Complete your essays for early round applications While the Common App essay gives admissions officers an insight into who you are, Supplementary essays like “Why This College/Major” showcase your keenness to join a college. So, don’t leave them for the last minute. Before writing them, thoroughly research the topic and colleges you wish to attend. 4. Fill out your FAFSA/CSS profile if you are applying for financial aid Check the deadlines and eligibility for financial aid and merit-based scholarships for colleges on your list and begin the application process. 5. Finalise your recommenders Speak to your school counsellor and teachers about your letters of recommendation. It is important to choose people who know you the best and can talk about your growth. Regards, Sheetal Vora Head of Undergraduate Admissions This email was sent to muskanmahajan2004@gmail.com why did I get this? unsubscribe from this list update subscription preferences The Red Pen · Prasad Chambers, #411 · Mumbai, MH 400004 · India

email subject: Creating an impactful application to your dream college
email body: Creating an impactful application to your dream college Dear Vikas, Applying to US colleges has become highly competitive, and with over 2000 institutions to choose from, selecting one that’s best for you can be daunting. That’s why a well-researched college list is the first step to simplifying the college selection process, and here’s how you can create one: 5 steps to creating a great college list for US undergraduate admissions What is demonstrated interest and how do I show it? Used by over 1000 colleges, the Common Application form enables you to highlight your strengths. You must showcase 10 activities within 150 characters and provide impactful letters of recommendation to highlight your uniqueness. Our blogs here will show you the best Common Application strategies: Everything you need to know about the Common Application How to draft a successful Common App activities section Letters of recommendation: Don’t leave them for the last Regards, Sheetal Vora Head of Undergraduate Admissions This email was sent to muskanmahajan2004@gmail.com why did I get this? unsubscribe from this list update subscription preferences The Red Pen · CHAMBER · Greater Mumbai, MH 400004 · India

email subject: Closing today: Applications for PG Diploma in Applied Statistics from Indian Statistical Institute
email body: Build in-demand skills in applied statistics and quantitative analytics In the Postgraduate Diploma in Applied Statistics, you will learn the statistical tools and concepts necessary to make data-driven decisions. You will also develop experience with statistical data analysis tools and acquire diverse skills required for roles that handle data analytics and applied statistics. Having a bachelor’s degree and fundamental knowledge of high school level mathematics are the only requirements to apply for this programme. What makes this PG Diploma special? Learn from world-class faculty: You will learn from the expert faculty who train officers of the Indian Statistical Service. You’ll also be able to clear your doubts through live sessions and emails. Learn how to manage, analyse, visualise, and present large data sets: You will acquire skills in scientific management of data to make data-driven decisions. Choose your specialisation: The programme, apart from instilling basic knowledge, also offers you a choice between two tracks - Official Statistics and Data Analytics, based on your area of interest. Real-world based learning: You will learn with real data from governments and organisations that are available in the public domain, for example, census data from the Ministry of Statistics and Programme Implementation. You will also explore case studies and learn to analyse data to solve real world problems. Last date to submit applcations is today. Apply now Have questions? Schedule a call with our admissions counsellor! About Indian Statistical Institute ISI functions under the Ministry of Statistics and Programme Implementation (MOSPI) of the Government of India and is involved in high impact projects involving large data and also trains the key officers of the ministry. email subject: Two days left to apply for PG Diploma in Applied Statistics from Indian Statistical Institute
email body: Build in-demand skills in applied statistics and quantitative analytics In the Postgraduate Diploma in Applied Statistics, you will learn the statistical tools and concepts necessary to make data-driven decisions. You will also develop experience with statistical data analysis tools and acquire diverse skills required for roles that handle data analytics and applied statistics. Having a bachelor’s degree and fundamental knowledge of high school level mathematics are the only requirements to apply for this programme. What makes this PG Diploma special? Learn from world-class faculty: You will learn from the expert faculty who train officers of the Indian Statistical Service. You’ll also be able to clear your doubts through live sessions and emails. Learn how to manage, analyse, visualise, and present large data sets: You will acquire skills in scientific management of data to make data-driven decisions. Choose your specialisation: The programme, apart from instilling basic knowledge, also offers you a choice between two tracks - Official Statistics and Data Analytics, based on your area of interest. Real-world based learning: You will learn with real data from governments and organisations that are available in the public domain, for example, census data from the Ministry of Statistics and Programme Implementation. You will also explore case studies and learn to analyse data to solve real world problems. Last date to submit applcations: 15 August, 2022 Apply now Have questions? Schedule a call with our admissions counsellor! About Indian Statistical Institute ISI functions under the Ministry of Statistics and Programme Implementation (MOSPI) of the Government of India and is involved in high impact projects involving large data and also trains the key officers of the ministry. ISI Kolkata has more than 250 faculty members who have achieved excellence in their research work. The contribution of the faculty has been recognized frequently with awards such as the Padma Shri Award, S. S. Bhatnagar Award, Fellowship of Indian Academy of Science to name a few. 18 scientists from ISI Kolkata got featured among the top 2% scientists in a global list compiled by the prestigious Stanford University in October 2021. email subject: Closing soon: Applications close on July 31st for the PG Diploma in Applied Statistics
email body: Submit your application by July 31st for the PG Diploma in Applied Statistics from Indian Statistical Institute In the Postgraduate Diploma in Applied Statistics, you will learn data analytics skills, develop an ability to distill information and clearly articulate your findings. You will also establish a solid foundation in applied statistics and learn the rigorous principles that guide statistical inference. What makes the PG Diploma in Applied Statistics special? Learn with real data from large government projects: Work with open databases used in policy and decision-making in public and private sectors. Gain expertise with specialized tracks: Choose between two concentrations of official statistics or data analytics depending on your interest. Learn how to analyze, visualize, and present large data sets: The programme is built around official data systems, and you’ll benefit from a 360-degree view into how these systems are built and used. Interact with and learn from globally recognised faculty: You will learn from the same faculty who teach the highly rigorous campus programmes at ISI and are also regularly engaged in the training of officers of the Indian Statistical Service. Programme duration: 12 months Fees: Rs. 4,50,000 / $ 6000 Last date to submit applcations: 31 July 2022 Classes start: 28 August 2022 Start my application Have questions? Please do not hesitate to get in touch by emailing us at pgdas.support@isical.ac.in About Indian Statistical Institute ISI functions under the Ministry of Statistics and Programme Implementation (MOSPI) of the Government of India and is involved in high impact projects involving large data and also trains the key officers of the ministry. ISI Kolkata has more than 250 faculty members who have achieved excellence in their research work. The contribution of the faculty has been recognized frequently with awards such as the Padma Shri Award, S. S. Bhatnagar Award, Fellowship of Indian Academy of Science to name a few. 18 scientists from ISI Kolkata got featured among the top 2% scientists in a global list compiled by the prestigious Stanford University in October 2021. email subject: Book a Private College Essay & Application Workshop for Your School
email body: Each year, my team and I deliver private college application & essay workshops for students in high schools and organizations around the world. ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ Hi friend, Each year, my team and I deliver private college application & essay workshops for students in high schools and organizations around the world (yay for Zoom). It’s part of our mission to provide access to high-quality essay support for any school, anywhere. Want to learn more about having a customized College Essay Guy workshop at your school or organization? A few highlights: Each workshop is designed for maximum engagement and participation Students will receive a workbook and access to our Choose Your Own Adventure essay revising tool Private workshops can be scheduled to meet your school or organization's unique needs and schedule We offer professional development (PD) workshops for teachers and staff Workshops start at $300. See Our Workshops Menu & Get in Touch Don't have a budget for a private workshop? I lead annual college essay and application workshops for high schools and organizations as part of my College Essay Guy LIVE program. To celebrate the opening for this year’s program, we're giving away 10 free private college essay & application workshops to a few schools/orgs that sign up for CEG LIVE before March 18 . Learn more here. Be well– Ethan Unsubscribe | College Essay Guy LLC, PO Box 250876, Glendale, California 91225, United States

email subject: Stanford Pre-Collegiate Summer Institutes: Applying for Financial Aid
email body: The deadline to apply is March 15, 2022. Need-Based Financial Aid Dear , Stanford Pre-Collegiate Summer Institutes is committed to equity and access. To ensure students of varying backgrounds, perspectives, and experiences have an opportunity to join our learning community, we offer financial assistance. If you are interested in applying for financial aid, please review the information on our Financial Aid page, linked below. We partner with School and Student Services (SSS) for our financial aid application. Please note that our financial aid application is separate from the program's admissions application. Both applications must be submitted by 11:59 pm (Pacific Time) on March 15, 2022 to be considered. Required documentation: Form 1040 and W-2 forms, along with any business tax forms International families who do not have the documentation above should submit documentation from their home country and the International Student Profile Form. Additional information for international families can be found here . More information about financial aid and instructions for the financial aid application can be found on our website . Should you have further questions, please do not hesitate to respond to this email. Sincerely, Stanford Pre-Collegiate Summer Institutes Team Stanford Pre-Collegiate Studies Academy Hall, 2nd Floor, 8851, 415 Broadway, Redwood City, CA 94063 precollegiate@stanford.edu

email subject: Your college application January to-do list (or, happy new year)
email body: Your college application January to-do list (or, happy new year) It's January, the final 6 months of your senior year. Center kindness. Dear Seniors – Happy New Year! Hopefully you were able to take some time over your school vacation to rest, relax, and recover from what was likely a stressful fall before starting back to school for this final stretch. For some of you, the college application process ended with confetti and an acceptance to your Early Decision school last month. For others, the process goes on as Regular Decision (or Early Decision 2) applications are completed and submitted in the coming days and the long wait of winter begins. There are a few things that are important for you to keep in mind this winter: 1. Trust your process! Recognize and appreciate the depth of the thoughtful and careful work you have been doing all summer and fall. While this time can feel challenging as you wait and feel like your fate is at the mercy of the college admissions offices, trust that you have done your very best work on your applications, that you have created a balanced list of schools, and that this will all work out! 2. Recognize that there is still time This might feel like the opposite of the point I just made. However, as you hear back from your Early Action schools this winter (many EA programs release decisions in late January), know that you can still find some wonderful likely schools to apply to this winter! There are many, many schools out there whose application deadlines might range from January 15th to February 15th (or even later). If you are curious about which schools those might be, first check your Common App deadlines, but also check out this comprehensive list of Late Application Deadlines (from the College Board ). 3. Know that you are not alone This is a moment to be graceful and lean into kindness as your friends and classmates reconcile their hard work on applications with admissions decisions that might or might not be what they had hoped. Now more than ever is the time to “choose kind” in your responses, to pause before you react or respond to a college acceptance celebration Insta post, and to applaud the successes that you see. Remember, it always works out – sometimes it just takes a little longer and goes on a slightly different path than you had planned. For more on this, check out this excellent blog post from the Georgia Tech Admissions Office (“ Applying to College is Not Like the Movies ”). 4. You only get one senior year! Seize this moment! You have about six months left in a high school career that has certainly not been the one you imagined at the beginning of 9th grade. COVID disruptions, Zoom school, socially distant proms, and canceled athletic seasons have all disrupted high school in different ways. In these last few months, seize opportunities to celebrate and make the most of this time you have left. Your high school class will never be together, fully, in this way again. Take opportunities to celebrate, be goofy, and enjoy this time together. 5. For the adults in your life, reflect on how you want to react to your child's admissions decisions Alas, it's behind a paywall, but if you have the opportunity to read this wonderful piece from Forbes “ Handling College Admissions Decisions: A Sidecar Parent’s Guide, ” Brennan Barnard offers some excellent (and timely) advice on how adults can and should respond as admissions decisions come in. That’s all for now! I’ll be back on April 1 with some more information about how to interpret and respond to the decisions that you have received (including information about managing the Waitlist). All my best and happy new year! Elise Elise London Elise spent fourteen years working as a high school college counselor in highly selective independent schools. She loves the college process for the ways it asks students to begin to articulate their purpose and their passions as they take the next step in their education. Cambridge Coaching 87 Nevins Street Brooklyn NY You received this email because you are subscribed to [2022] College Applicants from Cambridge Coaching. email subject: Your college application December to-do list (so, here we are at last)
email body: Your college application December to-do list (so, here we are at last) It's December. Either you'll be done soon or you'll keep chugging. Chin up. Center kindness. Hello there, Well, here we are! For some of you, December marks the official end of your months of research and hard work as an admission to an Early Decision school comes around. For others, December is just another month in a thoughtful and purposeful process. It is important this month to keep your chin up. As you hear about acceptances from classmates and peers, help them to celebrate even if you are processing a deferral or a rejection yourself. Remember, there are a lot of factors that go into a college application and decision. It is impossible to know why one classmate was admitted and another rejected. Please don’t make uninformed snap judgements about your peers. Remember back in August when we centered kindness? December is a wonderful time to resurface that emotion. If your college application process is continuing, here are some important tasks to complete in December: 1. Finish the supplements For many schools, January 1 is the deadline for all regular decision applications. If you are relying on the feedback of a teacher to support your writing, it is essential that you provide drafts to that teacher for comments well in advance of the winter school holiday. It is not fair to ask a teacher (or college counselor) to read and edit a supplement essay for you between Christmas and New Year. 2. Update your Common Application? You are allowed to make any edits or changes to your Common Application between submitting it in November and submitting it again to new schools in January. Do you have fall test scores to add? Have you changed your schedule? Do you have a new favorite activity? Take the time now to make sure that your Common Application is the best reflection of you that it possibly can be. 3. Consider Additional Information On the “Writing” page of your Common App, you should notice additional, optional spaces to include more writing. Here, you have the opportunity in a very open-ended way to share more information with the schools on your list. Remember, whatever you add here will be shared with all of the schools you apply to, so do not make this a statement that is specific to any one college. That said, you have 650 additional words to support or advocate for yourself. Do you have another essay you would like to share? Does it say something meaningfully different from your main essay? Take your time to consider what, if anything, you might want to include in the Additional Information section. 4. Manage Financial Aid applications Working with your family, be sure that you are ready to submit your FAFSA and, if needed, your CSS Profile and school-specific financial aid forms to the regular decision schools on your list. Some schools might send you additional financial aid paperwork (something like a “Federal Verification Form”) or ask you to submit a “Tax Transcript” in addition to your other paperwork. Follow the steps they indicate. If you have questions, remember that Financial Aid officers are people too, and you can always call them to make an appointment to talk this through. The FAFSA allows you to submit to only 10 schools at a time. If you have more than 10 schools on your RD list, do not worry! Submit your FAFSA to the first 10 schools. Wait 3-5 business days. Log back into your FAFSA and delete those schools (it has been sent to them now) and add the rest of your list. 5. Don’t forget a “Thank You” Your teachers worked hard to write thoughtful letters to support your college application process. Please take time in December to hand write them a thank you note. Be specific and gracious. If you feel comfortable doing so, keep them updated and in the loop as your decisions come out. At a minimum, please let them know where you are planning to matriculate! They care about you and about your success. Yes, this is a busy time, but know that you have got this! All of the careful work you have done already this year will make many of these tasks easy to complete. If you would like additional support on any of the above, please schedule a meeting with a member of the Cambridge Coaching team here . We love to make this process more manageable for students like you. All the best, Elise Elise London Elise spent fourteen years working as a high school college counselor in highly selective independent schools. She loves the college process for the ways it asks students to begin to articulate their purpose and their passions as they take the next step in their education.
